tiles.markdownText:
This dashboard is designed to **monitor workspace logs in near-real time** from the Monitoring Eventhouse.
It includes multiple pages, each dedicated to a specific workload.

The current starter page helps you review which workload logs are available in the connected Monitoring Eventhouse.

tiles.title: ðŸ”— Connect to multiple Workspaces
tiles.markdownText:
The templates support multiple monitoring scenarios.

Learn more about [multi-workspace monitoring architectures](https://github.com/microsoft/fabric-toolbox/tree/main/monitoring/workspace-monitoring-dashboards) listed on Fabric Toolbox, or download the [Power BI report template](https://github.com/microsoft/fabric-toolbox/tree/main/monitoring/workspace-monitoring-dashboards) for Workspace Monitoring.

tiles.title: Initial Steps
tiles.markdownText:
1. **Configure** the data source for this dashboard.

    _Hint: This dashboard supports defining multiple Monitoring Eventhouses using the "Workspace" parameter._

2. **Review** which workloads have logs available.

3. **Navigate** to one of the dashboard pages.

    _Hint: The pages are organized by workload._
